The Court.
890019 19 The Court.-
988400 1The constitution of the Court and the term of office of its members shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
1183353 2Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Court shall have the following powers and functions, namely:-
1704714 ato review, from time to time, the broad policies and programmes of the University and to suggest measures for the improvement and development of the University;
1309721 bto consider and pass resolutions on the annual report and the annual accounts of the University and the audit report on such accounts;
992211 cto advise the Visitor in respect of any matter which may be referred to it for advice; and
382759 dto perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
